{"title_page": "Attabotics", "text_new": "{{Use Canadian English|date = March 2020}}\n{{Short description|Robotics company}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date = March 2020}}\n{{Infobox company\n| name = Attabotics Inc.\n| logo = \n| logo_caption = \n| logo_size =\n| former_name = \n| type = [[Privately held company]]\n| owners = \n| foundation = {{start date and age|2016}}\n| founder = Scott Gravelle\n| num_employees = 210\n| num_employees_year = 2019\n| hq_location_city = [[Calgary]], [[Alberta]]\n| hq_location_country = [[Canada]]\n| area_served = \n| key_people = Scott Gravelle (CEO, CTO)\n| industry = [[Robotics]] design and manufacturing\n| products = \n| revenue = ~$30 million (2018)<ref name=jsmith/>\n| homepage = {{URL|attabotics.com}}\n}}\n'''Attabotics''' (stylized as ATTAbotics) is a [[Calgary]]-based robotics company which specializes in [[Inventory control|inventory management]] systems. Attabotics was named one of [[CNBC]]'s 100 most promising [[startup]]s in 2019<ref name=sheng>{{Cite web |last=Sheng |first=Ellen |title=Amazon\u2019s ant-size competition in designing the warehouse of the future |url=https://www.cnbc.com/2019/11/12/amazons-ant-size-competition-in-creating-warehouse-of-the-future.html |publisher=CNBC |date=2019-11-12 |accessdate=2020-03-30}}</ref> and ''[[Fast Company]]''<nowiki />'s 31st most innovative company in 2020.<ref name=fast>{{Cite web |last=Sorokanich |first=Lara |title=The World's 50 Most Innovative Companies: How a nature documentary inspired a cutting-edge design that shrinks massive warehouses into the space of an office building |url=https://www.fastcompany.com/90457446/attabotics-most-innovative-companies-2020 |work=Fast Company |date=2020-03-10 |accessdate=2020-03-30}}</ref>\n\nAttabotics designs and produces a robotic [[inventory]] storage and retrieval system.<ref name=parker/> The Attabotics system uses three dimensions of travel which greatly reduces warehouse [[Floor area|footprint]] and [[Human resources|workforce]] needed compared to a conventional [[fulfillment centre]],<ref name=compelling>{{Cite news |last=Livingstone |first=Barb |title=Compelling Calgarians: Scott Gravelle |url=https://calgaryherald.com/news/local-news/compelling-calgarians-scott-gravelle/ |newspaper=Calgary Herald |date=2020-01-02 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200107000411/https://calgaryherald.com/news/local-news/compelling-calgarians-scott-gravelle/ |archivedate=2020-01-07 |accessdate=2020-03-31}}</ref> and uses modular [[Container|tote]]s allowing the system to be easily scaled up or down.<ref name=robotreport>{{Cite web |last=Demaitre |first=Eugene |title=Attabotics brings vision of ant-like efficiency to supply chains |url=https://www.therobotreport.com/attabotics-brings-vision-ant-efficiency-supply-chains/ |work=The Robot Report |date=2019-08-16 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200330194411/https://www.therobotreport.com/attabotics-brings-vision-ant-efficiency-supply-chains/ |archivedate=2020-03-30 |accessdate=2020-03-31}}</ref> [[Nordstrom]]'s [[fulfillment centre]] in [[Newark, California]], which uses Attabotics and [[Tompkins Robotics]] systems, saved 90% floorspace compared to conventional alternatives.<ref name=thomas>{{Cite news |last=Thomas |first=Lauren |title=How Nordstrom uses robots and shelves inspired by ants to deliver lipstick faster |url=https://www.cnbc.com/2019/12/05/nordstrom-partners-with-attabotics-and-tompkins-robotics-for-faster-delivery.html |publisher=CNBC |date=2019-12-05 |accessdate=2020-04-01}}</ref>\n\nAttabotics had a total of $32.7 million in [[Seed funding|funding]] by 2019; investors included [[Coatue Management]], [[Comcast Ventures]], [[Honeywell Ventures]], [[Forerunner Ventures]], and [[Werklund Growth Fund LP]].<ref name=jsmith>{{Cite news |last=Smith |first=Jennifer |title=Logistics Automation Provider Attabotics Raises $25 Million in New Funding  |url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/logistics-automation-provider-attabotics-raises-25-million-in-new-funding-11564480801 |newspaper=Wall Street Journal |agency=Reuters |date=2019-06-30 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190801012614/https://www.wsj.com/articles/logistics-automation-provider-attabotics-raises-25-million-in-new-funding-11564480801 |archivedate=2019-08-01 |accessdate=2020-03-31}}</ref> Attabotics has also received government investment from [[Sustainable Development Technology Canada]]<ref name=cleantech>{{Cite web |title=$14.1 M for industrial clean tech investment |url=https://www.ippt.ca/14-1-m-for-industrial-clean-tech-investment/ |work=Industrial Process Products & Technology (IPP&T) |date=2018-04-12 |accessdate=2020-03-30}}</ref> and the [[City of Calgary]].<ref name=awarded>{{Cite news |last=Stephenson |first=Amanda |title=Robotic logistics company ATTAbotics awarded $4.5M from city's $100M fund |url=https://calgaryherald.com/business/local-business/robotic-logistics-company-attabotics-inc-awarded-4-5m-from-citys-100m-fund/ |newspaper=Calgary Herald |date=2018-12-12 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20191112123632/https://calgaryherald.com/business/local-business/robotic-logistics-company-attabotics-inc-awarded-4-5m-from-citys-100m-fund/ |archivedate=2019-11-12 |accessdate=2020-03-30}}</ref><ref name=dasilva>{{Cite news |last=DaSilva |first=Tomasia |title=Calgary robotic logistics company ATTAbotics Inc. gets $4.5M from city |url=https://globalnews.ca/news/4756313/calgary-robotics-company-attabotics-investment/ |publisher=Global News |date=2018-12-12 |accessdate=2020-04-04}}</ref>\n\nIn 2019, Attabotics announced a new headquarters building in Northeast Calgary.<ref name=parker>{{Cite news |last=Parker |first=David |title=Parker: ATTAbotics hires local company to design new building |url=https://calgaryherald.com/business/commercial-real-estate/parker-attabotics-hires-local-company-to-design-new-building/ |newspaper=Calgary Herald |date=2019-06-17 |accessdate=2020-03-30}}</ref> The design, by Calgary-based [[Modern Office of Design + Architecture]], won multiple architectural awards in 2019 and is expected to be complete in 2022.<ref name=moda>{{Cite web |title=Attabotics HQ |url=http://moda.ca/attabotics-hq/ |publisher=Modern Office of Design + Architecture |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200330195939/http://moda.ca/attabotics-hq/ |archivedate=2020-03-30 |accessdate=2020-03-30}}</ref><ref name=canarch>{{Cite journal |title=ATTAbotics Headquarters |url=https://www.canadianarchitect.com/attabotics-headquarters/ |work=Canadian Architect |volume=64 |number=12 |page=24 |date=December 2019 |accessdate=2020-03-30}}</ref><ref name=waf>{{Cite web |title=WAF 2019: Day 1 Winners Announced  |url=https://www.archdaily.com/929658/waf-2019-day-1-winners-announced |work=ArchDaily |date=2019-12-04 |accessdate=2020-04-04}}</ref> It is designed like a [[wedge]] to conform with nearby [[Calgary Airport]] height restrictions.<ref name=cao>{{Cite web |last=Cao |first=Lilly |title=MoDA's Attabotics Headquarters is Inspired by Ant Colonies |url=https://www.archdaily.com/926001/modas-attabotics-headquarters-is-inspired-by-ant-colonies |work=ArchDaily |date=2019-10-06 |accessdate=2020-03-30}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== Further reading ==\n*{{Cite news |title=Nordstrom partners with tech companies for faster delivery |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rr4WtXooSpo |publisher=CNBC Television |date=2019-12-05 |accessdate=}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://www.attabotics.com Official website]\n\n[[Category:2016 establishments in Alberta]]\n[[Category:Companies based in Calgary]]\n[[Category:Companies established in 2003]]\n[[Category:Technology companies of Canada]]\n[[Category:Canadian companies established in 2016]]\n[[Category:Technology companies established in 2016]]\n", "text_old": "{{Draft article}}\n{{Use Canadian English|date = March 2020}}\n{{Short description|Robotics company}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date = March 2020}}\n{{Infobox company\n| name = Attabotics Inc.\n| logo = \n| logo_c